.TH OB-CRYPT 1 "June 2026" "ob-crypt" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ob-crypt \- cryptographic toolkit for classical and modern ciphers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ob-crypt
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIcipher\fR [\fIinput\fR] [\fIparameters\fR]
.PP
.B ob-crypt \-\-list
.PP
.B ob-crypt \-\-help
.PP
.B ob-crypt detect [\-\-top \fIN\fR] [\fIoptions\fR] \fIinput\fR
.PP
.B ob-crypt analyze [\fIoptions\fR] \fIinput\fR
.PP
.B ob-crypt chain \-\-steps \fIsteps\fR [\-\-detect] [\fIoptions\fR] \fIinput\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Obscuron Crypto Suite's command-line interface. Reads input from an inline
argument, a file (\fB\-f\fR), or stdin and applies one of over 70 cipher
operations. Designed for speed with zero external dependencies (only the C++
standard library).
.PP
Output is printed to stdout. Combined with \fB\-\-hex\-input\fR and
\fB\-\-hex\-output\fR, the tool operates seamlessly in a Unix pipeline.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-raw
Machine-readable output \(em no labels or newlines.
.TP
.B \-\-hex\-input
Decode input from hexadecimal before processing.
.TP
.B \-\-hex\-output
Encode output as hexadecimal.
.TP
.B \-f \fIfile\fR
Read input from \fIfile\fR (binary-safe).
.TP
.B \-
Read input from standard input.
.TP
.B \-i \fIiv/nonce\fR
IV, nonce, or initialization vector (hex-encoded for AES/ChaCha20).
.TP
.B \-s \fIsalt/separator/shift\fR
Salt for KDFs, separator for A1Z26, or shift value for keyboard-shift/custom-rot.
.TP
.B \-\-iter \fIN\fR
Iteration count for KDFs (PBKDF2, Argon2id).
.TP
.B \-\-mem \fIN\fR
Memory cost in KB for Argon2id.
.TP
.B \-\-len \fIN\fR
Output length for KDFs, period for Trifid, or byte count for endian encoding.
.TP
.B \-\-counter \fIN\fR
Initial counter value for ChaCha20 (default 0).
.TP
.B \-\-secret \fItext\fR
Secret message to embed (for lsb-embed).
.TP
.B \-\-max \fIN\fR
Maximum key length for brute-force operations (default 10).
.TP
.B \-\-bits \fIN\fR
Bits per character for proper-base encoding (6=base64, 5=base32, 4=hex).
.SH SPECIAL MODES
.TP
.B \-\-list
List all available cipher names, one per line.
.TP
.B detect [\-\-top \fIN\fR] \fIinput\fR
Automatically detect which cipher was used. Returns top N candidates
(default 3) with confidence scores, decrypted text, and detected key.
.TP
.B analyze \fIinput\fR
Perform statistical analysis: detect encoding, compute length, Index of
Coincidence (IoC), Shannon entropy, byte distribution, and letter
frequencies.
.TP
.B chain \-\-steps \fIsteps\fR [\-\-detect] \fIinput\fR
Multi-step pipeline. \fIsteps\fR is a comma-separated list of operations:
.RS
.TP
.B base64
Base64 decode.
.TP
.B base16, hex
Hexadecimal decode.
.TP
.B caesar:\fIN\fR
Caesar shift by N.
.TP
.B vigenere:\fIkey\fR
Vigenere decrypt with \fIkey\fR.
.RE
.RS
With \fB\-\-detect\fR, runs cipher detection on the pipeline result.
Use \fB\-\-top\fR to control the number of candidates.
.RE
.SH CIPHER COMMANDS
.SS "Basic Ciphers"
.TP
.B caesar [\-s \fIshift\fR] \fIinput\fR
Caesar cipher. Shifts letters by \fIshift\fR (default 3). Negative
values shift backward.
.TP
.B rot13 \fIinput\fR
ROT13 \(em shift alphabet by 13 (self-inverse).
.TP
.B rot47 \fIinput\fR
ROT47 \(em shift all printable ASCII (33\(en126) by 47.
.SS "Hash Functions"
.TP
.B md5 \fIinput\fR
MD5 cryptographic hash (128-bit / 16-byte digest).
.TP
.B sha1 \fIinput\fR
SHA-1 cryptographic hash (160-bit / 20-byte digest).
.TP
.B sha256 \fIinput\fR
SHA-256 cryptographic hash (256-bit / 32-byte digest).
.TP
.B sha512 \fIinput\fR
SHA-512 cryptographic hash (512-bit / 64-byte digest).
.TP
.B blake2b [\-k \fIkey\fR] \fIinput\fR
BLAKE2b hash. Optional key (\fB\-k\fR) turns it into a MAC.
.TP
.B blake2s [\-k \fIkey\fR] \fIinput\fR
BLAKE2s hash (32-bit word variant). Optional key (\fB\-k\fR) turns it into a MAC.
.SS "Additional Classical Ciphers"
.TP
.B a1z26 [\-s \fIseparator\fR] \fIinput\fR
A1Z26 code \(em letters become their alphabet position (A=1, ..., Z=26). Default separator is \fB\-\fR.
.TP
.B bacon [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Baconian cipher \(em 5-bit binary encoding using A/B.
.TP
.B autokey \-k \fIkey\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Autokey cipher \(em Vigenere variant where the key extends with plaintext.
.TP
.B beaufort \-k \fIkey\fR \fIinput\fR
Beaufort cipher (reciprocal of Vigenere, self-inverse).
.TP
.B bifid [\-k \fIkey\fR] [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Bifid cipher \(em fractionating cipher using a 5x5 Polybius square. Default key is A-Z with I/J merged.
.TP
.B four-square \-k \fIkey1,key2\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Four-square cipher \(em digraph substitution using two keys. Same key for both if no comma.
.TP
.B keyboard-shift \-s \fIshift\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Shifts letters by N positions on a QWERTY keyboard layout.
.TP
.B keyword \-k \fIkeyword\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Simple substitution using a keyword-constructed cipher alphabet.
.TP
.B morse [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Morse code encoding/decoding (dots and dashes).
.TP
.B polybius [\-k \fIalphabet\fR] [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Polybius square \(em maps letters to row/column coordinates (5x5, I/J merged).
.TP
.B scytale \-k \fIrows\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Scytale transposition cipher \(em write in rows, read by columns.
.TP
.B substitution \-k \fI26\-\char key\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Simple substitution cipher \(em 26-letter key maps A\(rarrfirst, B\(rarrsecond, etc.
.TP
.B substitution-solve \fIinput\fR
Automatically solve a substitution cipher using frequency analysis. Outputs mapping and decrypted text.
.TP
.B trifid \-k \fIkey\fR [\-\-len \fIperiod\fR] [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Trifid cipher \(em 3D fractionating cipher on a 3x3x3 cube. Period defaults to 5.
.TP
.B adfgvx \-k \fIpolybius_key,col_key\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
ADFGVX cipher \(em fractionating cipher with 6x6 Polybius square and columnar transposition. Column key defaults to \fBADFGVX\fR.
.TP
.B binary [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Binary encoding \(em text to/from 8-bit binary strings.
.TP
.B braille [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Braille encoding \(em text to/from Braille Unicode characters.
.TP
.B octal [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Octal encoding \(em text to/from octal byte representation.
.TP
.B urlcode [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
URL encoding/decoding \(em special characters as %XX hex sequences.
.TP
.B rot8000 [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
ROT8000 \(em full Unicode rotation through the BMP.
.TP
.B custom-rot \-s \fIshift\fR \fIinput\fR
Rotate all characters by N (negative for reverse).
.TP
.B des3 \-k \fIhex_key\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Triple DES in ECB mode. Key is 24 bytes (48 hex chars).
.TP
.B hex-xor \-k \fIhex_byte\fR \fIinput\fR
XOR each byte with a single hex byte (00\(enFF).
.TP
.B str-xor \-k \fIstring\fR \fIinput\fR
XOR each byte with a repeating string key.
.TP
.B large \-b \fIbase\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Big-integer base encode/decode (combines base_encode/base_decode).
.SS "Historical / Classical Ciphers"
.TP
.B atbash \fIinput\fR
Atbash substitution \(em reverse alphabet (A->Z, B->Y, ...).
.TP
.B affine \-a \fImult\fR \-b \fIoffset\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Affine cipher \(em \fBE(x) = (mult * x + offset) mod 26\fR.
\fImult\fR must be coprime to 26.
.TP
.B vigenere \-k \fIkey\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Vigenere cipher \(em polyalphabetic substitution using \fIkey\fR as a
repeating keyword.
.TP
.B playfair \-k \fIkey\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Playfair cipher \(em digraph substitution on a 5x5 grid derived from
\fIkey\fR. Treats I and J as the same letter.
.TP
.B columnar \-k \fIkey\fR [\-\-decrypt] [\-\-len \fIL\fR] \fIinput\fR
Columnar transposition. Decryption requires \fB\-\-len\fR with the
original plaintext length.
.TP
.B railfence \-k \fIrails\fR [\-\-offset \fIN\fR] \fIinput\fR
Rail Fence zigzag transposition with \fIrails\fR rows and optional
\fIoffset\fR.
.TP
.B enigma \-r \fIrotors\fR \-o \fIoffsets\fR [\-p \fIplugboard\fR] \fIinput\fR
Enigma machine simulation. \fIrotors\fR and \fIoffsets\fR are
comma-separated integers (e.g., "1,2,3" and "0,0,0").
\fIplugboard\fR is colon-separated pairs: "0:1,2:3".
.SS "Encoding / Essential Ciphers"
.TP
.B xor \-k \fIhex_key\fR \fIinput\fR
XOR input bytes against \fIhex_key\fR (repeating). Specify the key as a
hexadecimal string.
.TP
.B base_encode \-b \fIbase\fR \fIinput\fR
Encode input as a big integer in \fIbase\fR (2\(en62). Uses O(1) memory.
.TP
.B base_decode \-b \fIbase\fR \fIinput\fR
Decode a big-integer base string back to raw bytes. Expects
lowercase letters for bases > 10.
.SS "Stream & Block Ciphers"
.TP
.B rc4 \-k \fIkey\fR \fIinput\fR
RC4 stream cipher (encrypt or decrypt \(em same operation).
.TP
.B des \-k \fIhex_key\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
DES block cipher in ECB mode. Key must be a hex string of exactly
16 hex digits (8 bytes, 56 effective bits).
.TP
.B blowfish \-k \fIkey\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
Blowfish block cipher in ECB mode. Variable-length key (1\(en32 bytes).
.SS "AES Block Cipher"
.TP
.B aes-ecb \-k \fIhex_key\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
AES in ECB mode. Key is 16, 24, or 32 bytes hex-encoded (32/48/64 hex chars). No IV.
.TP
.B aes-cbc \-k \fIhex_key\fR \-i \fIhex_iv\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
AES in CBC mode. IV must be 16 bytes (32 hex chars).
.TP
.B aes-ctr \-k \fIhex_key\fR \-i \fIhex_iv\fR [\-\-decrypt] \fIinput\fR
AES in CTR mode. Encrypt and decrypt are the same XOR operation.
.SS "ChaCha20 Stream Cipher"
.TP
.B chacha20 \-k \fIhex_key\fR \-i \fIhex_nonce\fR [\-\-counter \fIN\fR] \fIinput\fR
ChaCha20 stream cipher. Key is 32 bytes (64 hex chars), nonce is 12 bytes (24 hex chars). Encrypt and decrypt are the same operation.
.SS "Message Authentication"
.TP
.B hmac-sha256 \-k \fIkey\fR \fIinput\fR
HMAC-SHA256 message authentication code.
.TP
.B hmac-sha512 \-k \fIkey\fR \fIinput\fR
HMAC-SHA512 message authentication code.
.TP
.B poly1305 \-k \fIhex_key\fR \fIinput\fR
Poly1305 one-time MAC. Key is 32 bytes (64 hex chars). Produces a 16-byte tag.
.SS "Key Derivation"
.TP
.B pbkdf2 \-s \fIsalt\fR \-\-iter \fIN\fR \-\-len \fIN\fR \fIpassword\fR
PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA256 key derivation.
.TP
.B argon2id \-s \fIsalt\fR \-\-iter \fIN\fR \-\-mem \fIN\fR \-\-len \fIN\fR \fIpassword\fR
Argon2id key derivation (parallelism fixed to 1).
.SS "Token, Image & Encoding"
.TP
.B jwt-sign \-k \fIkey\fR \fIpayload\fR
Sign a JWT token. The same input is used as both header and payload JSON.
.TP
.B jwt-parse [\-k \fIkey\fR] \fItoken\fR
Parse and verify a JWT token. Key is optional (skips verification if omitted).
.TP
.B qr \fIinput\fR
Generate a text-based QR code (ASCII art grid).
.TP
.B lsb-embed \-\-secret \fItext\fR \fIcarrier\fR
Embed secret text into raw RGBA/RGB image bytes via LSB steganography.
.TP
.B lsb-extract \fIinput\fR
Extract hidden text from stego image bytes via LSB steganography.
.SS "Brute-Force"
.TP
.B brute-rotate \fIinput\fR
Try all 26 rotation shifts (0\(en25), including identity. Outputs
\fIshift: result\fR on each line. Use for generic rotation search.
.TP
.B brute-caesar \fIinput\fR
Try all 25 Caesar shifts (1\(en25) with multi-threaded execution.
Outputs \fIshift: result\fR. Traditional Caesar brute force without
the identity shift.
.TP
.B brute-railfence [\-\-max \fIN\fR] \fIinput\fR
Try Rail Fence ciphers with 2 to \fIN\fR rows (default 10).
.TP
.B brute-xor \fIinput\fR
Try all 256 single-byte XOR keys.
.TP
.B brute-vigenere [\-\-max \fIN\fR] \fIinput\fR
Try Vigenere decryption with key lengths 1 to \fIN\fR (default 10).
.SS "RSA Attacks & Utilities (requires NTL)"
.TP
.B rsa-decrypt \-c \fIvalue\fR \-d \fIvalue\fR \-n \fIvalue\fR
RSA decrypt: \fIm = c^d mod n\fR. All values accept hex (with or
without 0x prefix) or decimal.
.TP
.B rsa-wiener \-e \fIvalue\fR \-n \fIvalue\fR [\-c \fIvalue\fR]
Wiener's continued-fraction attack on RSA with small private exponent
\fId\fR. Outputs recovered \fId\fR, \fIp\fR, \fIq\fR. If \fB\-c\fR is
given, also decrypts via CRT.
.TP
.B rsa-hastad \-e \fIN\fR \-\-ciphertexts \fIcsv\fR \-\-moduli \fIcsv\fR
Hastad's broadcast attack. Recovers plaintext from \fIe\fR identical
encryptions under different moduli. Ciphertexts and moduli as comma-
separated hex values.
.TP
.B rsa-common-modulus \-n \fIvalue\fR \-e1 \fIvalue\fR \-e2 \fIvalue\fR \-c1 \fIvalue\fR \-c2 \fIvalue\fR
Recovers plaintext from two ciphertexts encrypted under the same
modulus \fIn\fR with coprime exponents \fIe1\fR, \fIe2\fR.
.TP
.B rsa-factor-fermat \-n \fIvalue\fR
Fermat factorization when the two primes \fIp\fR and \fIq\fR are
close together (\fI|p \- q| < n^{1/4}\fR). Up to 100000 iterations.
.TP
.B rsa-factor-pollard \-n \fIvalue\fR
Pollard's Rho heuristic factorization. Finds one non-trivial factor
of composite \fIn\fR using Floyd's cycle detection.
.TP
.B rsa-parity-oracle \-n \fIvalue\fR \-e \fIvalue\fR \-c \fIvalue\fR \-\-oracle \fIcommand\fR [\-\-timeout \fIms\fR]
Bleichenbacher-style LSB parity oracle attack. Pipes each query
ciphertext to \fIcommand\fR; expects \fB0\fR (even) or \fB1\fR (odd)
on stdout. Default timeout: 5000ms per query.
.TP
.B rsa-encode \-e \fIvalue\fR \-n \fIvalue\fR \fIinput\fR
RSA encrypt a plaintext string: \fIc = m^e mod n\fR. Converts each
character to its byte value, packs as a big integer, and exponentiates.
.TP
.B rsa-info \-n \fIvalue\fR [\-e \fIvalue\fR]
Analyze an RSA public key. Shows key size in bits, exponent quality
assessment (Hastad risk, small-exponent warning, non-standard large
exponent), Wiener attack feasibility estimate, trivial factor checks
(divisible by 3 or 5), and overall factorization difficulty.
.SS "Elliptic Curve Arithmetic (NTL)"
.TP
.B ec-add \-\-x1 \fIhex\fR \-\-y1 \fIhex\fR \-\-x2 \fIhex\fR \-\-y2 \fIhex\fR \-\-a \fIhex\fR \-\-p \fIhex\fR
Elliptic curve point addition on \fIy^2 = x^3 + ax + b\fR (mod \fIp\fR).
Input and output as hex strings.
.TP
.B ec-mul \-\-k \fIhex\fR \-\-x \fIhex\fR \-\-y \fIhex\fR \-\-a \fIhex\fR \-\-p \fIhex\fR
Elliptic curve scalar multiplication: \fIk * P\fR on
\fIy^2 = x^3 + ax + b\fR (mod \fIp\fR).
.SS "Discrete Logarithm (NTL)"
.TP
.B dlp-bsgs \-\-g \fIhex\fR \-\-h \fIhex\fR \-\-p \fIhex\fR
Baby-step giant-step discrete logarithm solver. Finds \fIx\fR such
that \fIg^x = h\fR (mod \fIp\fR). Time-memory tradeoff:
\fIO(sqrt(n))\fR.
.TP
.B dlp-pohlig \-\-g \fIhex\fR \-\-h \fIhex\fR \-\-p \fIhex\fR
Pohlig-Hellman DLP solver. Exploits smooth group order by solving
each prime-power subgroup via BSGS, then combining with CRT.
.SS "Lattice Reduction (NTL)"
.TP
.B lll \-\-matrix \fIjson\fR
LLL lattice reduction. Accepts a matrix in JSON-like format
\fB[[a,b],[c,d]]\fR. Outputs the reduced basis in the same format.
Uses NTL's floating-point LLL (FP variant) for speed.
.SS "Endian & Base Encoding"
.TP
.B little-endian [\-\-len \fIbytes\fR] \fIdecimal\fR
Encode an integer in little-endian byte order (default 4 bytes).
.TP
.B big-endian [\-\-len \fIbytes\fR] \fIdecimal\fR
Encode an integer in big-endian byte order (default 4 bytes).
.TP
.B proper-base \-\-bits \fIN\fR [\-k \fIalphabet\fR] \fIinput\fR
Chunk-oriented base encoding that preserves leading zeros. \fB\-\-bits\fR 6=base64, 5=base32, 4=hex.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Error \(em missing argument, unknown cipher, or I/O failure.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Caesar cipher (shift 7)
.B echo "hello world" | ob-crypt caesar -s 7
.TP
Caesar cipher (default shift 3)
.B ob-crypt caesar "khoor zruog"
.TP
ROT13
.B ob-crypt rot13 "uryyb jbeyq"
.TP
Atbash
.B ob-crypt atbash "svool dliow"
.TP
Vigenere encryption
.B ob-crypt vigenere -k secret "hello world"
.TP
Vigenere decryption
.B ob-crypt vigenere -k secret --decrypt "zincs pgvxi"
.TP
Affine cipher
.B ob-crypt affine -a 5 -b 8 "hello"
.TP
Affine decryption
.B ob-crypt affine -a 5 -b 8 --decrypt "rcllw"
.TP
Playfair
.B ob-crypt playfair -k keyword "hello world"
.TP
Columnar transposition encrypt
.B ob-crypt columnar -k zebra "attack at dawn"
.TP
Columnar transposition decrypt
.B ob-crypt columnar -k zebra --decrypt --len 14 "tkc aatdtaw n a"
.TP
Rail Fence
.B ob-crypt railfence -k 3 "hello world"
.TP
Enigma simulation
.B ob-crypt enigma -r "1,2,3" -o "0,0,0" -p "0:1,2:3" "HELLO"
.TP
XOR with hex key
.B ob-crypt xor -k "deadbeef" "plaintext"
.TP
RC4
.B ob-crypt rc4 -k "key" "plaintext"
.TP
DES
.B ob-crypt des -k "0123456789abcdef" --hex-output "plaintext"
.TP
Blowfish
.B ob-crypt blowfish -k "secretkey" --decrypt --hex-input "$(cat cipher.hex)"
.TP
Base64 encode
.B ob-crypt base_encode -b 64 "hello"
.TP
Base64 decode
.B ob-crypt base_decode -b 64 "aGVsbG8="
.TP
Cipher detection
.B ob-crypt detect --top 5 "uryyb jbeyq"
.TP
Statistical analysis
.B ob-crypt analyze -f ciphertext.bin
.TP
Chain: base64 decode then hex decode
.B ob-crypt chain --steps "base64,hex" "SGVsbG8="
.TP
Chain with auto-detect
.B ob-crypt chain --steps "base64" --detect "SGVsbG8="
.TP
Input from file, output as hex
.B ob-crypt \-\-hex\-output caesar \-f input.txt
.TP
Hex input from pipe
.B echo "68656c6c6f" | ob-crypt \-\-hex\-input caesar \-
.TP
List all ciphers
.B ob-crypt \-\-list
.TP
MD5 hash
.B ob-crypt \-\-hex-output md5 "hello world"
.TP
AES-256-CBC encrypt
.B ob-crypt aes-cbc -k "00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff" -i "0102030405060708090a0b0c0d0e0f10" "plaintext"
.TP
AES-256-CBC decrypt
.B ob-crypt aes-cbc --decrypt -k "00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff" -i "0102030405060708090a0b0c0d0e0f10" --hex-input "$(ob-crypt aes-cbc -k "00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff" -i "0102030405060708090a0b0c0d0e0f10" "plaintext")"
.TP
ChaCha20 encrypt
.B ob-crypt chacha20 -k "00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff00112233445566778899aabbccddeeff" -i "0102030405060708090a0b0c" "hello"
.TP
PBKDF2 key derivation
.B ob-crypt pbkdf2 -s "mysalt" --iter 100000 --len 32 "mypassword"
.TP
Sign a JWT
.B ob-crypt jwt-sign -k secret '{"sub":"123"}'
.TP
Single-byte XOR brute-force
.B ob-crypt brute-xor --hex-input "$(echo -n 'Hello' | ob-crypt xor -k '1b')"
.SH CIPHER INDEX
The following ciphers are available via
.BR "ob-crypt \-\-list" :
.PP
.ad l
.nf
a1z26        adfgvx       aes-cbc      aes-ctr      aes-ecb
affine       analyze      argon2id     atbash       autokey
bacon        base_decode  base_encode  beaufort     bifid
big-endian   binary       blake2b      blake2s      blowfish
braille      brute-caesar brute-railfence brute-rotate brute-vigenere
brute-xor    caesar       chain        chacha20     columnar
custom-rot   des          des3         detect       dlp-bsgs
dlp-pohlig   ec-add       ec-mul       enigma       four-square
hex-xor      hmac-sha256  hmac-sha512  jwt-parse    jwt-sign
keyboard-shift keyword     lll          large        little-endian
lsb-embed    lsb-extract  md5          morse        octal
pbkdf2       playfair     poly1305     polybius     proper-base
qr           railfence    rc4          rot13        rot47
rot8000      rsa-common-modulus rsa-decrypt rsa-encode
rsa-factor-fermat rsa-factor-pollard rsa-hastad rsa-info rsa-parity-oracle
rsa-wiener   scytale      sha1         sha256       sha512
str-xor      substitution substitution-solve trifid  urlcode
vigenere     xor
.fi
.ad
.PP
The names listed above follow the CLI names for the cipher operations
documented in this man page.
